values:
Well since the wonderful response to my engagement (barely a congratulations and hug and then everyone went back to talking about anything else) I asked my father tonight if he could give me away at our wedding. And he said that most likely he can't, and then suggested that Master and I won't be together by then anyway. I knew he didn't overly approve of our relationship, but really? I understand that he may not be able to travel from Australia to the US just to give me away, but following it up with "hey september next year is still a long time away, who knows if it will still be on" was not exactly what I was expecting.

And now Master wants us to go back to her hometown for the last couple of weeks of my visit... and bring her mama back with us. So not only will we not be alone and have to hide the truth of our relationship... when i break both our hearts AGAIN by leaving, we will be expected to be unaffected by it, since we're only friends. HOW THE FUCK AM I MEANT TO DO THAT?

So basically, this is all FUBAR and I have no idea how to make it work. *smiles wryly* at least I don't have to worry about an extensive guest list. We'll be lucky to have 5, including the bridal party.

Well here goes my second day at trying to write something daily. Apparently, most authors try to average at least 2000 words a day. That means I need to get myself into NaNo WriMo condition on a permanent basis. I really need to work on my writing space so that I have somewhere TO write. I don't really have space in my room for what I want, and it doesn't really help that I don't see this as home. I've only lived here fro the better part of 14 years, but I feel like a boarder, always intruding and imposing rather than feeling like it is "home". My inspiration, my home, is Master. That makes everything more difficult than I can possibly give words to. My muse is on the other side of the world, taking my desire to write with her.

To put it in a nutshell, perhaps where it belongs, since I am sure any of you reading this - indeed if anyone is in fact reading this, does not particularly care about any of what I am complaining about. Nor I am quite certain, do you care about any of my complaints or the end product - perhaps writing on a more continuous basis. I am trying my best to not disappoint master, but she pressures me to write so much, and I want to write.It is just rather difficult considering the depressing situation I am in, which is only compounded by my disappointing Master by not writing.

Maybe by arriving in three weeks will help with my writing. I was inspired to write constantly when I was in Master's presence, but merely did not have the opportunity. I think I may as well end my rant here, I'm not really saying anything new. I shall save my few (if any) readers the pains of further flogging of the proverbial dead horse.

Well.... apparently writing when you have nothing to say will get one in the habit of writing. So here is my attempt to regularly update my LJ in an attempt to write more often. Lets see how this works out because I have enough trouble writing when I DO have something to write about... Let alone when I have absolutely bollocks to write about. I have a real problem with procrastination when it comes to my writing. Especially lately when I have been finding every excuse to not write, and when I do sit down to write... What comes out onto the page is not great, and takes forever to get down. At this point I am willing to try this writing in my LJ daily to get into the habit of writing, if only to make me get more down on the page so Master is not so disappointed in my lack of progress in her book.

I have been managing about 500 words a day lately in my book that I am writing for Master, and it has now reached about 36,000 words total. Pam tells me that I don't need to be profound or deep in my daily ramblings but merely get in the habit of sitting down and writing for X amount of time per day. I don't have much faith in being disciplined enough to keep this up for long but I shall do my best. I want to make Master proud and finally present In The Fox's Lair to her. Completing this of course will allow me to continue with the Trilogy and then onto other works. But I think I am so resistant because Master keeps pushing me to write. She has such faith and confidence in my writing ability and I just don't see why.

On a completely unrelated note, I am heading back to the US for two months for Master's graduation. I can't wait, the last few months have been hell to be so far from her. It will be even more hellish to leave her again at the end of July. Goddess willing I will find some work that will let me return on a work visa so we are not at opposite corners of the globe. It will make it easier to look into our marriage too, come September next year. Well I think this ends my rambling for the day, lets see if it gets me writing more often...

Okay so National Novel Writing Month, or NaNo WriMo... WriMo for short... Starts next month and I am excited. Can't wait to get Immortal Night out there for everyone to critique! It will be interesting to see what regular - non friends people think of the story rather than what my friends have said. Its not that I don't value what they've said.... But honestly, how constructive is "yeah great story Mandy"? I am half prepared for it to go down in flames, but that is to be expected from this kind of thing. Look out Book Two eh? We'll see just how well this goes and how my writing develops over the course of the trilogy....

Okay my excited rant is over... back to work everyone

Got on the piss last night, and as I were in a happy mood, instead of going to bed when Chris left, I went out with them... The Shan was not too shabby, but then we all went on to C59...Now clubs so are not my scene, but it could not have been worse than the teeny bopper, Britney Spears type club that we went to.....it was utter agony.....left early to walk home (about three blocks) and now i am graced with a mild hangover and i am waiting until i shall be .00 so that I can drive to the laundromat and dry my washing...

I started back at uni today, and i fear it is going to be a very uneventful and boring semester.....and today, as in about an hour ago, I got back to Bendigo to see my Dad for about two weeks (missing next week of uni) but it will be worth it........ DAD FIX!!!!

My sister just called me (she did not answer yesterday eve when I called to tell her my University results) and after our usual slightly odd conversation of neither of us really knowing what to say to each other....She updates me on that not only is my bitch of a mother taking Dad to court, but she was not content with fifty percent, she now wants sixty-fory in her favour....does not matter that she does not deserve that....dad offered her fifty five/forty five in his favour and she turned it down, so he offered fifty/fifty, and she has turned that down too, and she friggin wants support payments....no matter that she has been in a relationship for a good nine months now and living off this new bloke....no she wants to take dad for every cent he has......selfish fucking bitch!!!! looks like my wish to not confront her until after university wont happen, court is set for 20th August....if she keeps up with this, she wont just lose Bec but me also!!!!!!  Sorry Mooie, if she keeps along this path I shall not be able to keep my promise to you

I received my university results for semester one this eve - two passes and two credits!!! I am so friggin stoked that I did not fail....especially after having to get special consideration for two units.....I PASSED THEM ALL - Granted two by the skin of my teeth....but i really do not care...i passed!!!

yesterday i bought a few books that i really could not afford, and the day before having my weekly talk with mother, who made me promise to let her pay for stuff, i told her i spent money and asked for fifty dollars, she gave me three hundred.....so not only do i feel terrible for using her like this, but she has made it so much worse for giving me so much, and i cannot even return it because i do not have her account details!!!! i feel so frigging guilty its not funny, but everyone is telling me that i should take what i can off her.....

The following quotes are from the Stephenie Meyer book "New Moon" and it perfectly describes where I have been, emotionally, for the last fifteen odd years, so here be the lines, and then what I have realised about them shall follow...
'I saw no reason for fear.  I couldn't imagine anything in the world that there was left to be afraid of, so physically at least.  One of the few advantages of losing everything"
'But I was getting better, and so the pain was something I could avoid for days at a time now.  The trade off was the never ending numbness.  Between pain and nothing, I'd chosen nothing'
'It was a crippling thing, the sensation that a huge hole has been punched through my chest, excising my most vital organs and leaving ragged, unhealed gashes around the edges that continued to throb and bleed despite the passage of time.  I curled inward, hugging my ribs to hold myself together.  I scrambled for my numbness, my denial, but it evaded me.  And yet, I found I could survive.  I was alert, I felt the pain - the aching loss that radiated out from my chest, sending waves of hurt through my limbs and head - but it was manageable.  I could live through it.  It didn't feel like the pain had weakened over time, rather that I'd grown strong enough to bear it'.
'I still hadn't been able to sink into my protective shell of numbness, and everything seemed oddly close and loud today, like I'd taken cotton out of my ears'
'I wondered how long this could last.  Maybe someday, years from now - if the pain would just decrease to the point where I could bear it - ....'
'But what if the hole never got any better?  If the raw edges never healed?  If the damage was permanent and irreversible?"

So they are the lines, and where I have been emotionally for most of my life, and after reading this book, I recognised the feeling that was being described.  It took about a week to realise exactly where this feeling had come from, and last night, talking to a friend, I remembered where I knew it from - the issues with my mother and the loss and pain is that conflict...I resort back to that closed off numbness whenever I speak with her, and the black hole is again wrenched open.  I know I need to sort all this out, but I feel it would not be wise until university is over, so I have another semester of her completely clueless of my thoughts about her, and me battling with what I am feeling... At least I am no longer at that place any longer, but I have just come through it all, and there are moments when I revert back to the numbness, well as close as I can get to it

I have just finished reading the two books Tim gave me - 'Twilight' and 'New Moon' by Stephanie Meyer and yet again it seems Djehuty is sending me the books that I require right now. First there were the Traci Harding books for spirituality (both for myself and my own story), then there was the Elita series for the mage battles (my story) and Robert Dunlorn's battle against a prophecy he was given at age nine, that rebelling against it and any emotions, not letting himself feel had created a blackness within him he called the Demon (for me).  And now there were the Stephanie Meyer books.  Other than the obvious physiological differences between Isabella (Bella) and myself, we seem to be very much alike, and the author's writing style was not just similar to my own and my mindspeech, but there were more subtle similarities.  Even though Bella desperately declared herself a coward, her actions proved the opposite, whereas I have declared that I am no coward, but my actions have shown me for what I truely am.    Also her relationship with Edward, the pain she described when he left, not only did I recognise that pain from my past, but I also felt shadows of that pain plagueing me throughout the day.  The gaping black hole/wound that was left is something I am more familiar with than I would care to admit, not to mention the four months of Bella being like a Zombie.  I must applaud her however, she was only that way for four months, I was there for fifteen years, and that gaping black hole is as dark as ever.  I have been fortunate enough to escape the nightmares though.  Do not get me wrong, I do get the occasional one, but luckily I am not one for talking in my sleep (as far as I am aware), I am susceptible to quite strange dreams, however.  All I know is that today, I cried when Edward left, as it were a reminder of my being left once before, and I felt the illness and depression settle over me.  There was no reason to call up the zombie-like numbness as that be too recent to be required.  And I am glad for both our sakes (Bella and my own) that we came out of it , although at least Bella has Edward, where I, as always, am alone, perpetually alone.  And as a final note, I could not escape the thrill and quickening of my own heartbeat at the prospect of being with one such as Edward, looks notwithstanding, the danger and excitement would be utterly irresistable.....And after that scarily long rant, I feel the need to add that I am not quite certifiable yet, I do know that these were fiction stories, just the parallels were kind of too scary to ignore....

Well it be over, and I shall hear back in about two weeks whether or not I was successful, although I believe it went quite well...must be due to my new shirt!!!! LOL ....but seriously i think i did ok, but apparently, i have a bubbly personality...who woulda thunk it eh?? i just decided to have Happy Amanda there, and she took over...and i guess was a little hyper....but i was me....not a nervous wreck either....but anyways there be no use in speculating further, i shall find out when i find out

I have a job interview in two hours and twenty-five minutes....and Murphy's Law is well and truely in place...First my printer was printing my resume really shittily, then I couldn't find my Certificate IV, then i went to get out my pants and it looked like someone had patted them with flour (still do not know how that one happened).  Then I went to Kmart to get new pants and a jacket...found the pants, got a new shirt because I could not find a jacket I liked.  Got home, went to put on my stocking sock thingys and could not find them, so now I have to wear my boots...Hunted down my black shoe polish to transform my brown blunnies into black ones...And at some time in the hunt, I grazed my arm, and its bleeding like a stuck pig...And has got a tiny bit of blood on my nice new shirt.....Its not much, but now I know its there its really annoying me....Lets just hope that Murphy's had his laugh, the sadistic bastard and everything will go well....its now down to two hours and twenty minutes

I cannot get to sleep, which is a bad thing as I have my Ethics exam in the morn and I need to be in fine form to get the 30/50 that i require to pass the unit.  Not writing for the last month has been taking its toll, especially the last two weeks as I have refused to write so that I may study for my exam, but it be getting more and more difficult to stop myself from writing, the urge is hard to supress.  At least. come Friday eve, I can write to my little heart's content because all my exams shall be finished and I will have three weeks off.

Something that has been playing on my mind of late (only Netjer knows why) is how I can be likened to a "Mutant from table five" out of "The Wedding Singer" as I have absolutely nothing to offer the opposite sex, and even if I did, I am that clueless as to how to be feminine that it is no longer funny!  I sometimes wish I had the confidence, lack of inhibitions (to some degree) that certain friends have (yes you LittleBrother), because at least that way I would be experiencing the world, rather than associating with people like that and wishing I had the courage to take the risk.  It would not be such a hopeless case if there were someone to help, but I cannot ask, because my lack of knowledge is actually laughable, I would just make a fool of myself - I cannot even put my hair in a pony tail successfully so how can I look appealing to a bloke?  Hell I do not even get second looks let alone have a guy buy me a drink - there are far more alluring girls out there than me, and it's not like I really bother, but still, it seems to be something that I have absolutely no aptitude for.  Why could it not be that I have no aptitude for math or science - but no, I have no aptitude at being exactly what I am - a female!!!  Kinda sad really....but anyways theres my rant for the minute...

I am bouncing around the lounge this morn, as I have just done my RPD and these be the results... I am a daughter of Heru-sa-Aset and my beloveds are Djehuty, Yinempu-Wepwawet and Hethert-Sekhmet!!! and this is my Akhu divination....
Em hotep! Your Akhu are speaking in the form of a reading named "the horse."
This is just the name of the reading. it doesn't have to mean anything to you, but I share it in case that it does.  What the reading actually means is this.  It's a strong reading, in the sense of aggressive. There is struggling going on in your life, and not necessarily violence, but hard stuff.  Force, a lot of force, is moving in your life.  Your Akhu say that you have every right to be proud of yourself and your life and to fight for yourself and what you want.  They say you are an aggressive person, and that you need to make sure you put your aggression into good places.  Act appropriately and you will get what you want. And They are promising to help you, too.  In terms of warning, you are being warned to work...but not too hard  you have a tendency to take on other people's problems and work and that's not right.  Heru is offering to help you with that, make offerings to Him if you need balance and also to your own ka (offering to your ka is a nice way to say do nice things for yourself)  The idea is that you're already in the midst of things, it's not something that is going to happen to you in the future just keep up, don't let yourself get too violent, and don't take on too much. there are a lot of strong happy Akhu here.

You scored as a III - The Empress
The Empress is a maternal symbol. She is the mother figure who loves, nurtures and protects. She will protect you, she will always be there when you are in trouble. When you fall over and graze your knee, the Empress will kiss it better. Yet she is not a weak figure. Her compassion is strength. If her children are threatened she will stop at nothing to protect them. If well aspected in a Tarot spread, the Empress can symbolise security, protection and unconditional love. If badly aspected it can represent over-protectiveness, fear of risk taking and refusal to face the real world.

The concert on Tuesday night was fan friggin tastic..... she is an awesome performer and i just had a bloody ball...thank you Mother for the tickets for Pam and myself...it was a great birthday present!!!

I do not know what I want to do with my life, do not get me wrong this course be interesting and great, and will give me a career, but I am just not sure it be the career i wish to have.  I have always wanted to help people, entertained the idea of joining the military or the police force, and do not misunderstand, people have to eat, and in a way, I am helping people working in Hospitality, but it is not quite what I have in mind.  I would also love to further myself spiritually, but do not have the means to do such an undertaking at this time.  This is leaving me at quite a loss as to what to do, I would love to teach but cannot see myself delivering classes in front of a group of youths.  So I am at a complete loss as to what I should do, and on that note I shall bid all my avid readers good day (pah...avid readers!)
I am bored shitless and cannot do anything, because any money that I have, has to be saved for the Pink concert on Tuesday night, and there be nothing I can do here GRRRRR

Physical pain is so much easier to deal with, it is something that I have always known, so it is any wonder, that being hte emotional cripple that I am, that I never cut.... But I just came to the realisation, that I never needed to when I was playing Basketball, I put my body through as much punishment as possible, not looking after myself, nor caring to..playing with dislocated fingers and knees, sprained ankles, torn hamstrings etc, just so that I had an outlet for all my anger and emotional baggage... Then all that went to hell in a handbasket when I was forced to give up basketball due to all that punishment, but I managed to hold myself together until now (5 years or so)...What I wouldn't give to pound the shite out of a basketball court once again!!!

I spoke to Greg today (my Ethics teacher) and he told me that I am entitled to 'Special Considerations' for all the shite that is going on with me at the moment, and as much as I want and need to do well in my coursework, I do not feel that I should receive it just because my head is MIA.....Don't get me wrong, I would be grateful for the assistance, but I would be all the more grateful for the return of my mind and the ability to do assignments

My head has left me these past weeks, I do not know where it has gone, but gone it definately has.  I cannot bring myself to write assignments, and even though I do, they are not of the quality I would like as, without my head, it be quite difficult to write them.  Two seven-days ago, I confronted an issue from my psat, as I had thought that that be the reason for my head being MIA, however that does not seem the case. So I was left to pick up the pieces of my scattered emotions from the confrontation, and now I am desperately in search of my head so that I can do this final assignment before Friday.

Finished my Organisational Behaviour assignment tonight, Mickle and I decided to work together - neither of us could be stuffed writing one each, so we both did it.....BUT THAT MEANS THAT I ONLY HAVE ONE LEFT TO GO!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

I just finished my second business ethics assignment, and have decided that ethics is evil....they are the biggest bastards of assignments to write, and after narrowly failing assignment one, i was somewhat reluctant to do assignment two...but needless to say, i have done it and am bloody glad i dont have to worry about it now until the exam!!!

I am feeling quite alone at the moment, despite being around family and friends for the past week.  I am looking forward to both Pam's and Thomas' birthdays, however, I lament their timing as it is a period of many assignments due.  Tonight I have decided to make a start on them, but how long this will last I do not know.  Although, when I think about these assignments, my dream of a plagiarised assignment comes to mind and the decision I was faced with, whether or not to follow the path of good or bad.  Whenever I think of this dream, I again consciously decide to follow the path of good.  It does not ease the stress, nor the loneliness, but I can take solace in the fact that I am nearing the end of my studies.  If only the loneliness birds would disperse, but they thoroughly enjoy taking up residence in my heart.

Self loathing is a strange thing.  It is your companion for so long that to part with it is indeed a trying ordeal.  Putting on a happy face and a smile for friends and family was such a common occurrence that it becomes second nature.  But when you decide to cast away such a pitiful existence, the walls come down one by one, making your more whole.  The walls, having protected you by keeping emotions at bay, are now fallen, leaving you to pick up the pieces of the scattered, unidentified emotions.  It is then that the self loathing comes back, making sure that it's full presence is known and that it will not be cast aside as easily as the walls at your feet.  It sits on your shoulder, every hour of every day, shouting every mistake ever made, every misdeed or unkindness committed.  It does not even let up when you sleep, whispering your unworthiness through your own acts of cowardice or anger.  It will not be easily denied, will not allow itself to be overcome, only content when you loathe yourself that much that you can barely function, and still you fight it, not really believing that you are worth the effort.  But mainly so that you will be able to hide your ugliness from those around you, desperately hoping that they do not see the utterly useless and unworthy coward that you are.
